        "client_msg_id": "dd6add07-eb0a-4179-b1d3-a1efc7c39bda",
        "text": "Thanks <@U02E4DAQGSZ>! So the answer to my question is \"An SPA, which happens to be a Lopecode notebook that you load in HTML format\".\n\nMy take on this is not \"hierarchical thinking\" but \"bootstrapping\". I have a browser that doesn't know about ATProto. And a notebook that's stored on a PDS. Something must connect the two.\n\nYour implementation of an AT loader is technically very elegant, but weird from a UX point of view, at least given today's UX expectations.\n\nAre there AT lexicons for code already? I see lots of possibilities there...",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "e169f54bbaf8",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2021-03-12\/1859691333940_e169f54bbaf8b9b36b12_72.png",
            "first_name": "Konrad",
            "real_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
            "display_name": "Konrad Hinsen",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "konrad.hinsen",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1775426582.816899",
        "parent_user_id": "U0AAJGPEPFC",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "C3H35",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Thanks "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "U02E4DAQGSZ"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "! So the answer to my question is \"An SPA, which happens to be a Lopecode notebook that you load in HTML format\".\n\nMy take on this is not \"hierarchical thinking\" but \"bootstrapping\". I have a browser that doesn't know about ATProto. And a notebook that's stored on a PDS. Something must connect the two.\n\nYour implementation of an AT loader is technically very elegant, but weird from a UX point of view, at least given today's UX expectations.\n\nAre there AT lexicons for code already? I see lots of possibilities there..."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1777364232.580389",
        "client_msg_id": "20e5b9b4-06fa-4b15-a44b-b102e32f2ae9",
        "text": "yeah, so the PDA store blobs WITH MIME TYPE. so you can store code files pretty easy as `application\/javascript` (or css\/html or *<https:\/\/www.digipres.org\/formats\/mime-types\/#text\/x-emacs-lisp|text\/x-emacs-lisp>) rather idiomatically* before you even hit the lexicon stuff.\n\n<https:\/\/tomlarkworthy.github.io\/lopecode\/notebooks\/atproto.html> is the bootstrapping solution, its the same code as `<at:\/\/did>:plc:j7nm3lrd5h7fm3sfhcv3lhfv\/dev.lopecode.bundle\/3mkjwz5coof2w`\n\nis \"<https:\/\/tomlarkworthy.github.io\/lopecode\/notebooks\/atproto.html> \" an SPA when it is also ``<at:\/\/did>:plc:j7nm3lrd5h7fm3sfhcv3lhfv\/dev.lopecode.bundle\/3mkjwz5coof2w``  ?\n\nYes its an SPA, but its also on the atmosphere. It is two manifestations of the same thing. Thats heirarchical thinking, when you try to put something in one box or another in a mutually exclusive way. Both places contain the same code base. It is not exclusively an SPA, but it can be an SPA if presented that way.\n\n\"but weird from a UX point of view\" this is a prototype, its not been refined at all, its just a conversation about a technical possability, not a final thing.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "27dffd0e73bd",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2021-09-13\/2483463922595_27dffd0e73bd6f709927_72.gif",
